Mix together the garlic, mint, mint sauce and yoghurt in a bowl, add the lamb and stir well. Cover and leave to marinate in a cool place for 10 minutes.Meanwhile, place the couscous in a heatproof bowl, pour 500ml/18fl oz of boiling water over the couscous. Leave to stand until the liquid has been absorbed. Season with salt and pepper and fluff the couscous with a fork. Set aside.Preheat the grill to a hot setting.Thread the lamb and onion and pepper wedges on to 8 metal skewers and cook under the grill for 8-10 minutes, or until cooked through.Serve the kebabs with lemon wedges and the couscous.